name: Potato-Crusted Salmon with Dill Tartar Sauce

steps.instruction:
### Prep
- Finely chop the dill
- Finely chop the green onion

### Steps
1. Preheat oven to 450°F
2. Chop dill and green onions (4 tablespoons); juice lemon (1 tablespoon)
3.  in small bowl: mayonnaise, relish, 1/2 teaspoon seasoning, lemon juice, dill, and 2 tablespoons green onions
4. Season salmon with remaining 1 teaspoon seasoning (wash hands)
5. Combine potato flakes, melted butter, and remaining 2 tablespoons green onions
6. Coat the top of each fillet with 1 tablespoon horseradish sauce, then press 1/4 cup potato mixture into sauce to adhere to each fillet
7. Line baking sheet with foil; bake fish 10–12 minutes or until topping has browned
8. Serve fish with sauce.
